@page
@model PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<h2>Our Privacy Policy</h2>
<partial name="~/Pages/Shared/_StatusMessage.cshtml" for="StatusMessage" />
<h2>Cookies</h2>
<h4>Background</h4>
<p>A cookies are small bits of text stored on your device and sent by your browser to the websites you visit. 
    Some of this information is necessary for you to use our website (Essential Cookies) whilst 
    other information may be used to personalize the content you receive (Functional Cookies), generate statistics 
    to help us optimize the operation of our website (Analytical Cookies), and for purposes like providing you with relevant
    adverts (Advertising Cookies). In addition to the cookies we manage ourselves (first party) you may also find cookies managed by
    trusted partners like Google Analytics (third party). Your acceptance of our Cookie agreement covers both first party and third 
    party Cookies stored on your device as a result of a visit to our website.</p>

<h4>Cookie Agreement</h4>
<p>Use of our website is dependent on you agreeing to our use of cookies, though you do have the option to refuse us permission to store
    certain cookies on your device; see <a href="#CookieManagement">Cookie Management</a>. We ask that you click the 'accept' button once 
    you've accepted the cookies you are willing to allow us (and others) to store on your device and also accepted this agreement. However, 
    if you are not prepared to accept these terms then you should <a href="#CookieManagement">delete any non-essential Cookies</a> we've already
    stored on your device and then close your browser to stop any further use of our site. In this case no cookies from our site should remain stored
    on your device after you close your browser. Please contact us if you experience any problems in this regard.</p>

<p><i>Note: People in the European Union benefit from <a href="https://github.com/wpqs/MxAutoGDPR/wiki/Backgroud:-Cookie-Law"  target="_blank">legal protection</a> in 
    respect of information like Cookies stored on their devices as consequence of using an electronic communication network like the internet</i></p>

<h4>Information about Cookies used on our website</h4>

<p>The following cookies are currently used by this website:</p>

<h6>Essential Cookies</h6>
<ul>
    <li><b>ARRAffinity</b>
        <ul>
            <li>Session Cookie</li>
            <li>Necessary for ensuring each user is always routed to the same machine when balancing the load of our webservers between different machines hosted on the Azure cloud.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>    
    <li><b>.AspNetCore.Antiforgery</b>
        <ul>
            <li>Session Cookie</li>
            <li>Necessary to make the website secure by preventing Cross-Site Request Forgery attacks.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>   
    <li><b>.AspNetCore.Identity.Application</b>
        <ul>
            <li>Session Cookie</li>
            <li>Necessary to authenticate users registered with the website.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li><b>.AspNetCore.Mvc.CookieTempDataProvider</b>
        <ul>
            <li>Session Cookie</li>
            <li>Necessary to store temporary data needed during a communication session.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>

<h6>Functional Cookies</h6>

<ul>
    <li><b>@PrivacyModel.ConsentCookieName</b>
        <ul>
            <li>Permanent Cookie expires after 365 days </li>
            <li>Necessary to allow non-essential cookies to be stored on your device. It also stops the Cookie banner from being
                display once a user has accepted our Cookie agreement.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>

<h6>Analytical Cookies</h6>

<ul>
    <li>No analytical cookies are currently used by this website</li>
</ul>

<h6>Advertising Cookies</h6>

<ul>
    <li>No advertising cookies are currently used by this website</li>
</ul>

<h6>Session Cookies</h6>

<p>Session Cookies should be deleted when a user's browser is closed so they only store information on a user's device whilst there is an active connection 
    with our website over an electronic communication network.</p>


<h6>Permanent Cookies</h6>

<p>Permanent Cookies are stored on a user's device whilst it is connected with our website over an electronic communication network, but are not deleted when 
    the connection terminates. Therefore the information they contain can be accessed during subsequent connections with our website. However, the information 
    will be deleted when the Cookie expires, typically after 365 days.</p>


<hr/>

<h4 id="CookieManagement">Management of Cookies</h4>

@if ((Model.EssentialCookies == null) || (Model.EssentialCookies.Count == 0))
{
    <p>No essential Cookies were found on your device for this website.</p>
}
else
{
    <p>The following list contains all the Essential Cookies passed by your browser to our website.</p>
    <ul style="list-style-type:none;">
        @foreach (var cookie in Model.EssentialCookies)
        {
            <li>@cookie</li>
        }
    </ul>
}
<br/>
@if ((Model.NonEssentialCookies == null) || (Model.NonEssentialCookies.Count == 0))
{
    <p>No non-essential Cookies were found on your device for this website.</p>
}
else
{
    <p>The following list contains all the non-essential Cookies passed by your browser to our website.</p>
    <form method="post">
        <input type="hidden" name="cookieList" value="@Model.CookieList"/>
        <ul style="list-style-type:none;">
            @foreach (var cookie in Model.NonEssentialCookies)
            {
                <li><input type="checkbox" name="@cookie"/>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;@cookie</li>
            }

        </ul>
        <button class="btn btn-primary"  type="submit">Delete</button>
    </form>
    <br/>
    <p>Please select the non-essential Cookies stored on your device that you want to remove and then click delete.</p>
}

<partial name="~/Pages/Shared/_Tip.cshtml" for="Tip" />

@section Scripts {
    <partial name="_ValidationScriptsPartial" />
}